Xiaomi unveiled its first 5G smartphone for the Chinese market the Xiaomi 9 Pro on Tuesday in Beijing. Photo: Zhang Hongpei/GTAlibaba, Ethiopia sign eWTP MoUEthiopia and Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba Group on Monday signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) to create the Electronic World Trade Platform (eWTP), which is believed to be a game-changing initiative for the digital economy of the East African country.MoU documents include those concerning the eWTP framework, digital capacity building and building a comprehensive digital hub.Stating that Ethiopia would be the gateway for Africa to join in on globalization because of its potential digital economy, Alibaba founder Jack Ma said, "The success of Ethiopia will not only inspire young Ethiopian people, it will also inspire the whole of Africa to grasp the opportunities of the digital economy," he said.Xiaomi sees robust growth in EuropeChinese tech firm Xiaomi saw robust growth in smartphone sales in the European market during the third quarter of the year, said a report from global technology market research firm Canalys.In the third quarter of 2019, Xiaomi had a market share of 10.5 percent with handset shipments reaching 5.5 million units, up from 3.2 million units during the same period last year.The growth was driven by aggressive market expansion and a strong volume product portfolio, read the report. Xiaomi ranked fourth in terms of shipments, after Apple, whose shipments reached 9.8 million units. 
